main event: A sighting took place at about 9:00 p.m. on May 9, 1952, 17 miles south of Fresno, California. The report states there were unusual lights in the sky which did not conform to normal aircraft lights. The lights reportedly maneuvered in an unusual manner, making sharp turns and accelerating rapidly. The lights were observed for approximately 10 minutes before disappearing.
interesting points: The sighting involved unusual lights in the sky that did not conform to normal aircraft lights.
The lights maneuvered in an unusual manner, making sharp turns and accelerating rapidly.
The lights were observed for approximately 10 minutes before disappearing.
The report was made by a civilian observer and subsequently investigated by the nearest Air Force base.
The investigator was unable to determine the nature of the unidentified lights and the case was classified as "Unknown" in the Project Blue Book files.
